ent.\n--- input ---\nindices, indptr: sparce matrix form of the Adjacency matrix\nedex_max: maximum number of elemental patch nodes\nndex_max: maximum number of nodal patch nodes\nElem_nodes: elemental connectivity stored in CPU as numpy array, (nelem, nodes_per_elem)\nnelem, nodes_per_elem, dim: scalar integers..\n--- output ---\nElemental_patch_nodes_st: elemental patch nodes, (nelem, edex_max)\nedexes: number of patch nodes for each element, (nelem,)\nNodal_patch_nodes_st: nodal patch nodes for each element, (nelem, nodes_per_elem, ndex_max)\nNodal_patch_nodes_bool: the same shape as Nodal_patch_nodes_st, returns 1 if the node has non-zero convolution patch function value, \n                        returns 0 if the node has zero convolution patch function value.\nNodal_patch_nodes_idx: the same shape as Nodal_patch_nodes_st, stores nodal index in the corresponding elemental patch nodes\nndexes: number of patch nodes for each node, and each element, (nelem, nodes_per_elem)"]}, {"name": "pyinn.Interpolator.NonlinearInterpolator.in_range", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xi", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lb", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ub", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns 1 when lb < xi < ub, 0 otherwise "]}, {"name": "pyinn.Interpolator.NonlinearInterpolator.get_R_cubicSpline", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xy", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xvi", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a_dil", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Cubic spline radial basis function "]}, {"name": "pyinn.Interpolator.NonlinearInterpolator.get_R_gaussian1", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xy", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "xvi", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a_di